    "description": {
      "value": "<p>Under the circumstances listed in the monster&rsquo;s stat block&mdash;such as when it makes a full attack or a rend attack&mdash;it can immediately attempt an additional attack against an opponent. This attack is made using the creature&rsquo;s full base attack bonus, plus any modifiers appropriate to the situation. This additional attack doesn&rsquo;t stack with similar means of gaining additional attacks, such as the <a class=\"entity-link\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; background-image: none; background-color: initial; padding: 0px; color: #ff6400; border: none;\" draggable=\"false\" data-pack=\"pf1.spells\" data-id=\"s9amdo5398alb5p0\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; text-decoration-line: underline;\">haste</span></a> spell or a speed weapon. This ability doesn&rsquo;t grant an extra action, so you can&rsquo;t use it to cast a second spell or otherwise take an extra action in the round.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em>Format</em>: feral savagery (full attack)</p>\n<p><em>Location</em>: special attacks.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
